solution.p:
			This is not a subspace.

          \begin{bmatrix}1\\1\\1\end{bmatrix}

        is in it, but

          5\begin{bmatrix}1\\1\\1\end{bmatrix}

        is not.

statement.p:
Let W be the subset of \Mvec_{2,2}(\mathbb{R}) given by

  W=\left\{
  \begin{bmatrix}a\amp b\\c\amp d\end{bmatrix}
  \ \middle|\ a,b,c,d\in \mathbb{R},\ a+b=c+d
  \right\}.

Is W a subspace of \Mvec_{2,2}(\mathbb{R})?

Show that the sets

  S=\{x+2,(x+2)^2\}

and

  T=\{x^2-4,x^2+x-2\}

span the same subspace of \mathbb{P}_2.

Show that the sets

  S=\left\{
  \begin{bmatrix}1\amp0\\0\amp1\end{bmatrix},
  \begin{bmatrix}0\amp1\\1\amp0\end{bmatrix}
  \right\}

and

  T=\left\{
  \begin{bmatrix}1\amp1\\1\amp1\end{bmatrix},
  \begin{bmatrix}1\amp-1\\-1\amp1\end{bmatrix}
  \right\}

span the same subspace of \Mvec_{2,2}(\mathbb{R}).
